Subject: [PATCH] tests: cover popen `--` shim fix and two-tier implicit-rule
 selection
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Two regression tests for the busybox-build fixes:

- testcase/implicit_rule_prefer_existing.mk: a kati↔make conformance case for
  the two-tier implicit-rule selection. app.o matches both `%.o: %.c` and
  `%.o: %.S`; the .c prerequisite is directly available (mentioned target) while
  the .S one is only obtainable by chaining `%.S: %.gen`. GNU make and rkati must
  both compile from app.c. Corpus is now 365/379 (fail=0), parallel-equiv
  365/365.

- test_brush_nested_sh_rs.py case 10: feeds the exact argv shape glibc's
  popen(3) produces, `/bin/sh -c -- CMD`, and asserts the `--` terminator is
  skipped (not run as a command) and the recipe actually executes.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01XyA6FzC6QGgsrjEYEBJV46
---
 testcase/implicit_rule_prefer_existing.mk | 24 +++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 24 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 engine/vendor/kati/testcase/implicit_rule_prefer_existing.mk

diff --git a/testcase/implicit_rule_prefer_existing.mk b/testcase/implicit_rule_prefer_existing.mk
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..b9a8051
--- /dev/null
+++ b/testcase/implicit_rule_prefer_existing.mk
@@ -0,0 +1,24 @@
+# Two-tier implicit-rule selection. app.o matches both `%.o: %.c` and
+# `%.o: %.S`. The `.c` prerequisite is "available" (app.c is a mentioned
+# target), while the `.S` prerequisite is only obtainable by chaining another
+# pattern rule (`%.S: %.gen`). GNU make prefers the rule whose prerequisite is
+# directly available over one needing an intermediate, so it must compile from
+# app.c and never assemble a generated app.S. (This is busybox's
+# applets/applets.o: a `%.o: %.S` rule and a catch-all link rule make the bogus
+# applets.S look producible, but applets.c exists and must win.)
+all: app.o
+
+%.o: %.c
+	@echo CC $@ from $<
+
+%.o: %.S
+	@echo AS $@ from $<
+
+app.c:
+	@echo CREATE $@
+
+%.S: %.gen
+	@echo GEN $@ from $<
+
+app.gen:
+	@echo CREATE $@
